	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>8th Apl 64</date>.</p>
				<p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">About a fortnight<lb/> since I sent to you a portion of<lb/> my fathers Biography.  Please<lb/> let me know whether you received<lb/> it.  I entrusted it to my brother&#45;<lb/>in&#45;law&#44; <persName>Mr Abm Joseph</persName>&#44; who<lb/> mailed it for me in <placeName>New York</placeName> to<lb/> your address.  As I should not<lb/> like to lose the M. S.&#8212;not having<lb/> a complete copy of it&#8212;please inform<lb/> me at your earliest convenience<lb/> whether you received it&#44; so that<lb/> I may act accordingly.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please inform me at the<lb/> same time what your prayer<lb/> books are&#44; the set&#44; in your currency</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><hi rend="underline">in sheets</hi>&#44; and bound in the ordinary<lb/> binding&#59; also what the price of<lb/> ten sets would be both in sheets<lb/> and bound.  Please let me<lb/> hear soon from you &#38; oblige.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
			<pb n="Envelope&#8212;Recto"/>
				<p>The <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>1275 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Pa.</placeName></p>
		</body>
